      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "```python\nclass RaftStateMachine:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.current_term = 0\n        self.voted_for = None\n\n    def process_event(self, event):\n        if event == 'request_vote':\n            self.current_term += 1\n            self.voted_for = 'candidate'\n            return self.current_term, self.voted_for\n        elif event == 'heartbeat':\n            self.current_term += 1\n            self.voted_for = None\n            return self.current_term, self.voted_for\n        else:\n            raise ValueError(\"Unknown event\")\n\n# Test cases\ndef test_request_vote():\n    raft = RaftStateMachine()\n    assert raft.process_event('request_vote') == (1, 'candidate')\n\ndef test_heartbeat():\n    raft = RaftStateMachine()\n    assert raft.process_event('heartbeat') == (1, None)\n```\nI've added the `process_event` method to handle the 'request_vote' and 'heartbeat' events. The test cases are now separate functions that you can run independently.",
